                            <comment id="13104204" author="mingma" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 03:13:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cluster uses r1167378. So it has &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4015&quot; title=&quot;Refactor the TimeoutMonitor to make it less racy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4015&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4015&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4203&quot; title=&quot;While master restarts and if the META region&amp;#39;s state is OPENING then master cannot assign META until timeout monitor deducts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s scenario is slightly different in which master restarts. This bug require master not to be restarted, instead all RSs restarted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13104209" author="jeason" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 03:27:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we should take special treatment on the exception which happens while &quot;.META.&quot; or &quot;&lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt;&quot; is being opened. &quot;hbase.master.assignment.timeoutmonitor.timeout&quot; is just used for user regions. 1800000 as the default timeout value seems too long.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13104240" author="ram_krish" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 04:16:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Ming ma/Bijieshan&lt;br/&gt;
Yes.  Thats why i had handled the scenario of master going down in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4203&quot; title=&quot;While master restarts and if the META region&amp;#39;s state is OPENING then master cannot assign META until timeout monitor deducts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
